I wasn't being entirely serious about offering to install
nameservers/mailers for anyone, but it is probably true that the
startup delays in doing such a thing would be long.

So far, all the systems from which I've had people commenting/
complaining have been UNIX boxes.  That's the most surprising aspect,
since the required tools for UNIX machines are so readily available.

Where can I get a copy of the MILNet conversion schedule?  I'd like to
see in some detail just how long one can anticipate MILNet being so
far behind, and thus how long I'll be getting these questions.

So far, I am indeed just telling people "not my problem," but it has
varying effects on the requestors.

--Karl

